what I needed to say.

596
00:29:31,870 --> 00:29:33,394
Of course I can.

597
00:29:33,538 --> 00:29:35,165
[elevator dings]

598
00:29:35,306 --> 00:29:37,069
[Kate] Oh, can you hold
that elevator?!

599
00:29:37,208 --> 00:29:40,143
Can you...? Oh! Thank you!
Can you scooch over a little?

600
00:29:40,278 --> 00:29:42,803
Sorry, it's my daughter's
sixth birthday tomorrow,

601
00:29:42,947 --> 00:29:45,916
and I was just afraid the bakery
and balloon place would close,

602
00:29:46,050 --> 00:29:47,881
so I went at lunch.

603
00:29:48,019 --> 00:29:50,510
Great. Can someone
push lobby for me?

604
00:29:50,655 --> 00:29:52,714
Thank you.

605
00:29:52,857 --> 00:29:54,290
All in?

606
00:29:55,994 --> 00:29:56,858
[balloon pops]

607
00:29:56,995 --> 00:29:58,519
Everyone knows the right way

608
00:29:58,663 --> 00:29:59,994
to throw a birthday party.

609
00:30:00,131 --> 00:30:02,031
You call Ernesto
at Playtime Events.

610
00:30:02,167 --> 00:30:05,193
He handles everything.
The letter-pressed invitations,

611
00:30:05,336 --> 00:30:07,099
the balloons, all perfect.

612
00:30:07,238 --> 00:30:09,263
And if you slip him an extra 50,

613
00:30:09,407 --> 00:30:12,342
he will even send your in-laws
the wrong address

614
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:14,707
so that they end up just driving
around the city all day,

615
00:30:14,846 --> 00:30:16,404
and then they show up right
at the end of the party.

616
00:30:16,548 --> 00:30:17,276
[doorbell rings]

617
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:19,881
- Hi, honey.
- [Richard] Mom, Dad, hi, come on in.

618
00:30:20,018 --> 00:30:21,280
- Oh!
- [woman] Hi, Kate.

619
00:30:21,419 --> 00:30:23,649
- [Richard] How's it going?
- Hi!

620
00:30:23,788 --> 00:30:27,053
- Hi. Thank you for coming.
- Our pleasure.

621
00:30:27,192 --> 00:30:29,592
Oh, that's very sweet.
Good to see you.

622
00:30:29,727 --> 00:30:31,354
- Good to see you.
- That's lovely. Thanks.

623
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:33,487
So, um, can l
get you guys a drink?

624
00:30:33,631 --> 00:30:37,123
- [Emily] Oh, no!
- [crashing]

625
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:42,670
Or some candy?

626
00:30:43,341 --> 00:30:45,707
- Do you have any soda for the kids?
- No, no soda, Mom.

627
00:30:45,844 --> 00:30:47,038
Too much sugar.

628
00:30:47,178 --> 00:30:49,373
Yeah, and dried fruit is out.
It rots their teeth.

629
00:30:49,514 --> 00:30:53,177
Last year, the nursery school
issued a fatwa on raisins.

630
00:30:53,318 --> 00:30:56,810
- And yet you have a pinata.
- Well, you know, that's different.

631
00:30:56,955 --> 00:31:00,721
That's, um... That's, uh...
culturally enriching.

632
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:02,918
- Ah.
- Mm-hm.

633
00:31:03,061 --> 00:31:04,426
[woman] Here's some water,
sweetie.

634
00:31:04,562 --> 00:31:06,086
- [Emily] Thanks, Grandma.
- She thinks we're ridiculous.

635
00:31:06,231 --> 00:31:08,495
'Cause we are, a little.

636
00:31:08,633 --> 00:31:10,191
You OK?
You seem a little off today.

637
00:31:10,335 --> 00:31:12,462
Me? Yeah.
I'm great, why?

638
00:31:13,738 --> 00:31:17,367
- [doorbell rings]
- The, uh, savages have arrived.

639
00:31:17,508 --> 00:31:19,874
I'll get the door.

640
00:31:20,011 --> 00:31:21,842
Wait, Richard, Richard.
We need to talk.

641
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:23,277
- [doorbell rings]
- Now?

642
00:31:24,249 --> 00:31:25,978
Uh, no, OK, later.

643
00:31:26,117 --> 00:31:28,017
Of course, you're right.
Later.

644
00:31:28,152 --> 00:31:30,245
- What is it, Kate?
- No, it's just... You know what?

645
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:34,415
It's just a thing. Honestly, it's no
big deal. We'll discuss it later.

646
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:38,086
- You sure?
- Yeah, yeah, go. Open the door.

647
00:31:38,229 --> 00:31:41,062
I'm really sorry, but New York
liked my idea for the retirement fund.

648
00:31:41,199 --> 00:31:43,167
- They want me to develop it further.
- [kids chatter outside]

649
00:31:43,301 --> 00:31:46,464
Which means that I will be really busy
and traveling for the next two months.

650
00:31:46,604 --> 00:31:48,333
[girl] Let me in!

651
00:31:50,174 --> 00:31:52,005
Is that cake made
with organic flour?

652
00:31:52,143 --> 00:31:53,041
- Yep.
- Thanks.

653
00:31:53,177 --> 00:31:54,701
We got a diaper change!

654
00:31:54,846 --> 00:31:56,143
Clothing change.

655
00:31:56,281 --> 00:31:58,078
Oh, they need to be boiled.

656
00:31:58,216 --> 00:31:59,808
Hey, we need to talk
about that thing later.

657
00:31:59,951 --> 00:32:01,680
Yep, can't wait.

658
00:32:04,555 --> 00:32:06,614
Are you guys having fun?

659
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:09,420
He really is incredible
with them, isn't he?

660
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:11,425
- Yeah.
- I know when our kids were little,

661
00:32:11,562 --> 00:32:13,792
