678
00:32:56,674 --> 00:33:00,303
He's almost two
and not one real word.

679
00:33:01,179 --> 00:33:02,874
Doesn't that bother you?

680
00:33:06,317 --> 00:33:09,480
And the worst part is she's right, you
know? I mean, about Ben not talking.

681
00:33:09,620 --> 00:33:13,556
By this age, Emily was reciting the
first chapter of Canterbury Tales

682
00:33:13,691 --> 00:33:16,353
in Middle English,
and all Ben does is grunt.

683
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:18,689
Kate, that's fine.
We gotta talk about the fact...

684
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:22,493
Richard, Richard, I know.
I know it's lousy timing for both of us.

685
00:33:22,633 --> 00:33:24,863
To get a big project at work
at the same time, I know that.

686
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:27,301
But we can make it work.
I know we can.

687
00:33:27,438 --> 00:33:30,339
And I'm gonna do my very best
to make sure that

688
00:33:30,475 --> 00:33:32,409
nothing falls through the cracks.

689
00:33:33,311 --> 00:33:35,074
Look, Richard,

690
00:33:35,213 --> 00:33:39,513
you have been working so hard
to get a big break at work. Me, too.

691
00:33:39,650 --> 00:33:43,177
It's a great problem.
We can do this.

692
00:33:43,321 --> 00:33:45,312
- We just have to do a little juggling.
- I know.

693
00:33:45,456 --> 00:33:47,822
- But if we're...
- I promise I will make everything work.

694
00:33:47,959 --> 00:33:49,654
- Don't worry.
- OK, but I'm just telling you...

695
00:33:49,794 --> 00:33:51,625
I said don't worry!

696
00:33:52,463 --> 00:33:56,923
